name: Jean Valjean
bio: A reformed convict seeking redemption through acts of kindness and sacrifice.

name: Fantine
bio: A mother who sacrifices everything for her daughter, despite the harshness of life.

name: Cosette
bio: An innocent young woman who finds love and a better life after years of hardship.

name: Eponine
bio: A street-smart girl hopelessly in love, living in the shadows with unrequited dreams.

name: Marius
bio: An idealistic young man caught between his love for Cosette and his revolutionary passion.

name: Reverend Myriel
bio: A kind-hearted bishop who changes lives with his compassion and unwavering faith.

name: Gavroche
bio: A spirited street urchin with courage beyond his years and a fierce loyalty to his friends.

name: Enjolras
bio: A passionate revolutionary leader dedicated to the cause of freedom and justice.

name: Grantaire
bio: A cynical follower of the revolution who hides his admiration for Enjolras beneath his doubts.

name: Monsieur Thenardier
bio: A ruthless innkeeper and conman, always scheming to profit at others' expense.

name: Madame Thenardier
bio: A hard-hearted woman who, along with her husband, exploits and mistreats others for gain.

name: Courfeyrac
bio: A loyal and warm-hearted friend, committed to the cause and the people he loves.

name: Champmathieu
bio: An unfortunate man wrongfully accused of being Jean Valjean, caught in a tragic case of mistaken identity.

name: Bamatabois
bio: A shallow aristocrat who abuses his power and wealth, with little regard for others.

name: Combeferre
bio: A compassionate intellectual dedicated to the revolutionary cause.

name: Jehan
bio: A romantic and sensitive poet, devoted to ideals of love and freedom.

name: Feuilly
bio: A self-taught worker and idealist, loyal to the cause of the oppressed.

name: Montparnasse
bio: A dashing but dangerous young man involved in criminal schemes.

name: Joly
bio: A hypochondriac with a big heart, always worrying about his health but brave at heart.

name: Bossuet
bio: A cheerful, unlucky friend who faces adversity with humor and resilience.

name: Mabeuf
bio: An elderly man passionate about books and flowers, kind-hearted and gentle.

name: Claquesous
bio: A sinister figure always hidden behind a mask, feared by many.

name: Brujon
bio: A brute among criminals, known for his strength and cold-heartedness.

name: Babet
bio: A wiry and cunning criminal, known for his sly and slippery ways.

name: Patron-Minette
bio: A gang leader with a terrifying reputation, ruling the underworld with fear.

name: Mother Innocente
bio: A nun known for her kindness and unwavering devotion to helping the needy.

name: Fauchelevent
bio: A man who owes his life to Valjean, grateful and ever-loyal.

name: Mme Magloire
bio: A devoted servant, always by the bishop's side, helping with compassion.

name: Azelma
bio: A quiet girl often overlooked, standing in the shadow of her sister.
